Show a vector v = ai_hat + bj_hat.

As 'a' and 'b' values change, animate the i_hat and j_hat scaling and their sum (tip-to-tail method).

To visualize 'Span', leave a trail of points (dots) where the resultant vector 'v' lands.

Transition: Show a case where i_hat and j_hat are parallel (e.g., and ) and demonstrate that the 'Span' collapses from a 2D plane to a 1D line.

Module 3: Linear Dependence (3D Perspective)
